        "description": "Provenance REQ: jn79an6qv3j60bq64c8mekwjkx83tprp\n\nnoscope mint outputs scoped token to stdout for caller to deliver (SSH, k8s secret, API call). noscope revoke explicitly revokes a previously minted token. Decouples credential lifecycle from local subprocess management.\n\nRules:\n- NS-060: Mint output envelope — JSON to stdout: token (string), expires_at (ISO 8601), token_id (provider-supplied or UUID), provider, role\n- NS-061: Revoke CLI input contract — accept --token-id+--provider or full mint JSON via --from-stdin; token values never as CLI args (NS-012)\n- NS-062: Mint mode TTL requirement — --ttl required; no refresh/revocation unless explicit noscope revoke; caller responsibility after mint\n- NS-063: Mint multi-provider atomicity — follows NS-006; output is JSON array or nothing on failure; no partial stdout\n- NS-064: Redaction exception for mint stdout — NS-005 does not apply to mint stdout (by definition contains token); still applies to stderr/logs\n- NS-065: Terminal detection for mint — if stdout isatty, warn to stderr and exit 64 unless --force; tokens in scrollback are a risk\n\nProvenance stats: 3 resolutions, 6 rules",
