Implemented `noscope-ofd` end-to-end with strict TDD, including a red phase with failing tests first, green implementation, refactor, Linus-style self-review, and final commit (not pushed).

- Added a new core module at `src/token_provider.rs` with:
  - `TokenProvider` trait: object-safe, `Send + Sync`, async-style `mint(role, ttl)`, `refresh(token)`, `revoke(token)` via boxed futures (NS-015).
  - `TokenProviderError`, `TokenProviderFuture`.
  - `CleanupOnDropFuture` + `with_mint_cleanup(...)` so dropped mint futures can run cleanup handlers (NS-018).
- Refactored `ScopedToken` in `src/token.rs` to a metadata-backed core shape:
  - Fields now center on `value`, `role`, mandatory `expires_at`, and `metadata`.
  - Secret remains `secrecy::SecretString`; `Clone` is still not implemented (NS-016).
  - Kept compatibility accessors (`provider()`, `token_id()`) backed by metadata.
- Re-exported new primitives from `src/lib.rs` so consumers can use them directly from crate root.
- Added dedicated rule tests in `src/token_provider.rs`:
  - `ns_015_token_provider_method_signatures_object_safe_send_sync`
  - `ns_016_scoped_token_mandatory_expiry_and_zeroizing_type`
  - `ns_017_refresh_returns_new_token_and_does_not_mutate_existing`
  - `ns_018_*` coverage for drop cleanup behavior and non-trigger on successful completion
- Linus-style review fix applied:
  - Identified API gap where NS-018 cleanup wasn’t easy to apply uniformly; added `with_mint_cleanup(...)` and extra edge-case tests to make usage explicit and verifiable.
- Posted provenance update on requirement `jn7e50xjb2j4gp6b5vpjz2qw8x83t1ax` via `statesman provenance thread post`.

